sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM), where a total of 44,546 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 4.5 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 64.6% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month of 6.9 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $72.50 strike call option expiring September 23, 2016 , with 4,664 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 466,400 underlying shares of CRM.

Thor Industries, Inc. (Symbol: THO) saw options trading volume of 4,043 contracts, representing approximately 404,300 underlying shares or approximately 64.4% of THO's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 628,235 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $90 strike call option expiring October 21, 2016 , with 2,007 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 200,700 underlying shares of THO.

Below is a chart showing THO's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $90 strike highlighted in orange:

And National Beverage Corp. (Symbol: FIZZ) options are showing a volume of 1,935 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 193,500 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 63.5% of FIZZ's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 304,515 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $50 strike call option expiring October 21, 2016 , with 783 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 78,300 underlying shares of FIZZ.
